    - For numbers greater than 3, the function checks divisibility from 5 up to the square root of the number, incrementing by 6 each step (i.e., it checks 5, 11, 17, etc.).

2. **checkAndPrintPrimes Function**:
    - This function takes an array of 5 numbers as input.
    - It first checks if the array has exactly 5 numbers; if not, it throws an error.
